definitions.definition: A part broken off; a small, detached portion; an imperfect part, either physically or not
examples: a fragment of an ancient writing
I heard a small fragment of the conversation.

definitions.definition: A sentence not containing a subject or a predicate; a sentence fragment .
A portion of a URL referring to a subordinate resource or anchor (such as a specific point on a web page ), introduced by the # sign.
examples: The URL www.example.com/home#recent ends with a fragment .

definitions.definition: A split piece of an organism that has undergone the asexual reproduction process where the organism spilts into one or more pieces, then those pieces become new individuals.

main_definition: A part broken off; a small, detached portion; an imperfect part, either physically or not
secondary_definitions: ( grammar ) A sentence not containing a subject or a predicate; a sentence fragment .
( computing ) An incomplete portion of code .
( Internet ) A portion of a URL referring to a subordinate resource or anchor (such as a specific point on a web page ), introduced by the # sign.
( biology ) A split piece of an organism that has undergone the asexual reproduction process where the organism spilts into one or more pieces, then those pieces become new individuals.
